<br>
So what do you guys think of the class tree itself?<br>
<br>
I myself am a little wary.  I dunno, I think I'm just wary of combat in EQ2 in general, but moreso after this list for some reason.<br>
<br>
I mean... let's take combat in EQ1.  Can I see a show of hands for how many people think that EQ1 standard combat (group of people + a healer slugging it out with a monster) is fun?<br>
<br>
When I think fun combat in EQ1, I think of things like kiting, and fear kiting with a group, and AE battles, etc.  Standard fighting is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>really</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> boring to me.  It's just like push button 1, push button 2, ho hum, yawn, etc, repeat.  <br>
<br>
In EQ2, it sounds like this is exactly the scenario they're forcing people into.  You can't fight in any manner except a group with a good range of classes slogging it out, hit button 1, push button 2, yawn, ho hum, etc.  Sure, they're adding some special ninja moves or whatever, but ultimately it really feels like they're draining any sense of strategy out of it.<br>
<br>
   bleh.<br>
<br>
   We'll see what people think come beta time, but I'm actually quite concerned about this aspect of EQ2.  Fantasy MMORPGs are won or lost on the battlefield, and an ass-boring battle system will just kill a game, cuz that's what people spend most of their time doing.<br>
<br>
