Yep that's exactly what they are doing.  I think you might be misguided with the lack of strategy comment.  They are almost removing the one on one encounters that EQ1 is famous for.  Any adds were crowd controlled by chanters or offtanked by pally's.  Now different strategies will have to be developed to have successful encounters with most mobs in the game.  I look at it like a breath of fresh air in an almost stagnant area in EQ 1.  Personally I believe this will open up so much more of the RP and emersion(sp?) into the game than the current EQ1 allows.  Now you can Roleplay to your heart's content and no one will be able to say &quot;We HAVE to have such a class for such and such zones&quot;  You can use any alternatives and they basically get the job done but with benefits <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
