<br>
So when it comes to sneaking around, disarming traps, etc, every rogue can do it, whether they're brigand or swashbuckler or troubador or ranger, etc.<br>
<br>
So, in terms of creating a successful party, any party which has at least 1 priest, 1 mage, 1 warrior, 1 rogue will be do fine, regardless of what class/subclass everyone is.  More specialized combos might do better, but I heard that any group that meets the above should be able to function okay.<br>
<br>
But as I said, that again is what makes me worry that combat will have very little strategy to it.  I don't really consider timing special attacks and stuff to be strategy, but we'll see.  I can't really criticize it w/o having experienced it.<br>
<br>
